The change in voltage across the air void is calculated as follows: VAir=VTotal1+tInsulatortAir×εInsulator
Where
VAir is the voltage across the air void;
VTotai is the voltage applied across the modified insulation barrier;
tInsulator and tAir are the sizes of the PTFE-based component and air void respectively;
εInsulator is the dielectric relative permittivity of the PTFE-based component.
